main event: A civilian in Germantown, Tennessee observed a pulsating light that appeared to be an aircraft in the sky for 5-8 minutes on December 12, 1968.
interesting points: The observer reportedly photographed the pulsating light, but no photographs were included in the report.
The observer described the object as a 'pulsating light' that seemed to be an aircraft.
The object was visible for several minutes, traveling from ENE to SSW.
The report mentions 'map photographs' and 6-8 shots, but no photographs were present in the document.
The observer was asked to complete an AF Form 1321 and submit the original negatives, slides, or Polaroid prints for further investigation.
photographs: yes, but not included in the report
